               <msContents>
                  <summary>I) Introduction (fols. 3ra-17rb)&#xD; - Maqdǝma Wangel “Introduction to
                     the Gospels” (fols. 3ra-9vb)&#xD; - Letter of Eusebius to Carpianus (fols.
                     9vb-10rb)&#xD; - Canon tables (fols. 10ra-16ra)&#xD; - On the reliability of
                     the Gospels (fol. 17ra-17rb)&#xD; - Statement about the Eusebian sections (fol.
                     17rb)&#xD; - List of the “tituli” for the Gospel of Matthew – 69 titles (fol.
                     17rb-vb)&#xD; - Biography of John (fol. 18ra-rb)&#xD; - List of the “tituli”
                     for the Gospel of John – 20 titles (fols. 18rb)&#xD; II) Gospel of Matthew
                     (fols. fol. 17rb-vb, 19ra-71vb)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta Mātewos “Gospel of Matthew”
                     (fols. 19ra-71vb) &#xD; - Postscript (fols. 71vb)&#xD; III) Gospel of Mark
                     (fols. 72ra-106rb)&#xD; - Biography of Mark (fol. 72ra-72rb)&#xD; - List of the
                     “tituli” for the Gospel of Mark – 48 titles (fols. 72va-73ra)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta
                     Mārqos “Gospel of Mark” (fols. 74ra-105vb)&#xD; - Postscript (fols.
                     105vb-106ra)&#xD; - Extended opening formula (of biography of Luke?) (fols.
                     106ra-106rb)&#xD; IV) Gospel of Luke (fols. 106va-160vb)&#xD; - Biography of
                     Luke (fol. 106va-106vb)&#xD; - List of the “tituli” for the Gospel of Luke – 83
                     titles (fols. 107ra-108ra)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta Luqās “Gospel of Luke” (fols.
                     109ra-160vb&#xD; V) Gospel of John (fols. 18r, 161ra-217vb)&#xD; - Bǝsrāta
                     Yoḥannǝs “Gospel of John” (fols. 161ra-217vb)&#xD; - Postscript (fol.
                     217ra-217vb)&#xD; &#xD; Additio: 1.</summary>
